f the overall figures for Wirral. Numbers of beneficiaries for Birkenhead using postcode data are provided. All eligible people are contacted by the Healthy Start Issuing Unit and are invited to apply. The Department also publicises the scheme via the Healthy Start website and helpline.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2015-10-19T14:53:12.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420155/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420155/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420155/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2015-10-09","Healthy Start Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what proportion of eligible people took up Healthy Start vouchers in (a) Birkenhead, (b) the Liverpool, city region and (c) the UK in the last period for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","10933"
