"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420252","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-19","<p>Details of Ministers' and Permanent Secretaries meetings with external organisations are published up to 31 March 2015 and can be accessed on Gov.uk at:<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications</a></p><br /><p>Further publications of Ministerial and Permanent Secretaries meetings will be published in due course.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-10-19T16:37:50.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420252/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420252/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420252/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-09","Ministry of Justice: Pressure Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what meetings (a) Ministers and (b) officials in his Department have had with representatives of (i) the Taxpayers' Alliance, (ii) the Confederation of British Industry, (iii) the Institute of Economic Affairs, (iv) the Adam Smith Institute, (v) the Freedom Association, (vi) the Politics and Economics Research Trust and (vii) the Midlands Industrial Council in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","11181"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420253","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-29","<p>The annual operating costs were approximately:</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Name</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Operating Costs 2014/15</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>BOSTON MAGISTRATES' AND COUNTY COURT</p></td><td><p>£195,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>LINCOLN MAGISTRATES' COURT</p></td><td><p>£300,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>SKEGNESS MAGISTRATES' COURT</p></td><td><p>£198,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>The consultation closed on 8 October and no final decisions will be made until all consultation responses have been carefully considered.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-10-29T10:54:34.733Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420253/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420253/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420253/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-09","Magistrates' Courts: Lincolnshire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the estimated annual operating costs of (a) Lincoln Magistrates' Court, (b) Skegness Magistrates' Court and (c) Boston Magistrates' Court are when calculated using the same methodology as for his Department's consultation on the court and tribunal estate.","false","Biography information for Stephen Phillips","Sleaford and North Hykeham","Stephen Phillips","11182"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420254","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-16","<p>No decision will be taken on the future of Grantham Magistrates' Court until the responses to the consultation have been considered.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-10-16T10:54:02.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420254/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420254/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420254/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-09","Magistrates' Courts: Grantham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what the estimated market value is of the freehold buildings used by Grantham Magistrates' Court.","false","Biography information for Stephen Phillips","Sleaford and North Hykeham","Stephen Phillips","11183"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420255","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-14","<p>On 1 October 2015, the government published a consultation on Preserving and Enhancing the Quality of Criminal Advocacy, which sets out a package of measures designed to ensure the quality of criminal defence advocacy. These proposals seek to address the concerns highlighted by judges and legal practitioners, as well as Sir Bill Jeffrey in his Review of Independent Criminal Advocacy, published in May 2014. This consultation will close on 27 November this year and the government is keen to listen to all views on the proposals.</p>","North West Cambridgeshire","Mr Shailesh Vara",,"2015-10-14T15:19:08.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420255/answer","Biography information for Mr Shailesh Vara","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420255/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420255/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-09","Legal Representation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, pursuant to his oral contribution of 8 September 2015, Official Report, column 222, what progress he has made on talks with the Bar and the solicitors' profession on maintaining access to justice and enhancing the quality of advocacy in courts.","false","Biography information for Meg Hillier","Hackney South and Shoreditch","Meg Hillier","11103"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420256","Home Office","false","2015-10-14","<p>The Home Office does not currently hold the information requested. The latest statistics covering arrests for notifiable offences by gender, age and police force area cover the period to the year ending 31 March 2014, and can be found here: https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2014/police-powers-and-procedures-england-and-wales-year-ending-31-march-2014#arrests.</p><p>Arrests data covering the period to the year ending 31 March 2015 are due to be published on Thursday 19th November 2015.</p><p>Data covering the period requested, and up to the year ending 31 March 2016 will be published in 2016.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-10-14T16:44:58.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420256/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420256/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420256/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2015-10-09","Arrests: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many women and girls (a) under 17, (b) 18 to 20, (c) 21 and over, (d) of unknown age and (e) in total were arrested for notifiable offences in the North Wales police force area (i) in 2015-16 to date and (ii) in the most recent quarter.","false","Biography information for David Hanson","Delyn","Mr David Hanson","11122"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420257","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-16","<p>This information could only be provided at disproportionate cost.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2015-10-16T11:15:15.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420257/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420257/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420257/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-09","Religiously Aggravated Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many religious leaders have been convicted for contravening the (a) Public Order Act 1986, (b) Criminal Justice and Public Order Act 1994, (c) Racial and Religious Hatred Act 2006 and (d) Criminal Justice and Immigration Act 2008 for crimes against (i) Muslims, (ii) Jews, (iii) Israelis and (iv) Christians.","false","Biography information for Mark Pritchard","The Wrekin","Mark Pritchard","10986"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420258","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-15","<p>Since they transitioned to new owners on 1 February 2015, Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs) have been contractually required to maintain a professional and appropriately skilled workforce to deliver the services set out in their contracts. The Ministry of Justice (MoJ) does not currently maintain data relating to posts and staffing levels in CRCs</p><p><br>CRCs are responsible for their own staff training needs, such as for managing female offenders. As part of their bids, the new owners were required to put forward plans to ensure female offenders are properly supported. Similarly, it is for CRCs to decide on appropriate job titles for their staff</p><p><br>The MoJ closely monitors the performance of CRCs, in line with government standards, to make sure they fulfil their contractual commitments to maintain service delivery, reduce reoffending and deliver value for money to the taxpayer.</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous","10955 ; 10956 ; 10957","2015-10-15T15:24:25.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420258/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420258/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420258/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-09","London Community Rehabilitation Company: Vacancies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many posts at which levels are vacant in the London Community Rehabilitation Company.","false","Biography information for Sir David Amess","Southend West","Sir David Amess","10954"
