"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420268","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-16","<p>Information on IEP levels for all prisoners by prison function is published annually in the management information addendum of the NOMS Annual Report. The table below shows the number of young people on basic level of the IEP scheme as at the end of March 2015 in all the under 18 Young Offender Institutions.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Cookham Wood</p></td><td><p>Feltham</p></td><td><p>Werrington</p></td><td><p>Wetherby</p></td><td><p>Parc</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>23</p></td><td><p>50</p></td><td><p>19</p></td><td><p>28</p></td><td><p>58</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Please note that Feltham and Parc are split sites so data provided is inclusive of young adults</p>","South West Bedfordshire","Andrew Selous",,"2015-10-16T10:30:57.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420268/answer","Biography information for Andrew Selous","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420268/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420268/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-09","Young Offenders: Prisoners' Incentives and Earned Privileges Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many children were on the basic level of the IEP scheme in (a) HM Young Offender Institution Feltham, (b) HM Young Offender Institution Wetherby, (c) HM Young Offender Institution Werrington, (d) HM Young Offender Institution Cookham Wood and (e) Parc Young People's Unit on the latest date for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Jenny Chapman","Darlington","Jenny Chapman","11254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420269","Northern Ireland Office","false","2015-10-19","<p>Details of Ministers' and Permanent Secretaries meetings with external organisations are published up to 31 March 2015 and can be accessed on Gov.uk at: https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications.</p><p>Further publications of Ministerial and Permanent Secretaries meetings will be published in due course.</p>","Wyre and Preston North","Mr Ben Wallace",,"2015-10-19T12:05:23.313Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420269/answer","Biography information for Mr Ben Wallace","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420269/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420269/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2015-10-09","Northern Ireland Office: Pressure Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what meetings (a) Ministers and (b) officials in her Department have had with representatives of (i) the Taxpayers' Alliance, (ii) the Confederation of British Industry, (iii) the Institute of Economic Affairs, (iv) the Adam Smith Institute, (v) the Freedom Association, (vi) the Politics and Economics Research Trust and (vii) the Midlands Industrial Council in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","11178"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420270","Prime Minister","false","2015-10-14","<p>A reply will be sent shortly.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-10-14T15:41:16.12Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420270/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420270/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420270/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-10-09","Prime Minister: Correspondence","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, when he will reply to the letter of 24 July from the First Minister of Scotland on the surveillance of Members of the Scottish Parliament; and if he will place in the Library a copy of his response.","false","Biography information for Ian Murray","Edinburgh South","Ian Murray","10842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420271","Prime Minister","false","2015-10-14","<p>A wide range of national security issues, including energy security, are considered by the National Security Council and the NSC (Threats, Hazards, Resilience and Contingencies) sub-Committee. Senior officials support and inform these Ministerial-level discussions.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-10-14T16:48:40.81Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420271/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420271/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420271/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-10-09","Energy: Infrastructure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what assessment the National Security Council has made of the potential risks of using Chinese-built or owned energy infrastructure.","false","Biography information for Sir Bernard Jenkin","Harwich and North Essex","Mr Bernard Jenkin","11209"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420272","Prime Minister","false","2015-10-16","<p>The UK has long been clear that we would only consider using our nuclear weapons in the most extreme circumstances of self-defence.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-10-16T12:23:07.043Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420272/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420272/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420272/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-10-09","Trident","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, under which criteria the Government would consider it justified to launch (a) a pre-emptive nuclear attack on another independent state or states using the Trident nuclear weapons system based in Scotland and (b) a retaliatory nuclear attack on another independent state or states using the Trident nuclear weapons systems based in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Dr Paul Monaghan","Caithness, Sutherland and Easter Ross","Dr Paul Monaghan","11054"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420273","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-10-19","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) decided in January 2000 to allow lesbian, gay, bisexual and transgender (LGBT) personnel to serve openly in the UK Armed Forces. Since that time the Department has been working to create a more inclusive culture where everyone feels valued, regardless of their sexuality. The inclusion of all three Services in Stonewall's 2015 list of the top 100 employers for LGBT personnel is testament to our success in this arena.</p><p>At the time of our decision in 2000 to change the policy on serving LGBT personnel there were four legal cases brought by LGBT personnel against the MOD which had reached the European Court of Human Rights (ECHR). The ECHR ruled against the MOD and compensation was paid in full. Employment Tribunal applications on the same subject were also settled at the time and compensation was paid. There are no plans to provide further compensation.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-10-19T15:47:05.677Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420273/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420273/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420273/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-10-09","Armed Forces: LGBT People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans the Government has to acknowledge and compensate for the damage caused to individuals as a result of the former ban on homosexual people serving in the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","11119"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420274","Prime Minister","false","2015-10-16","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the Written Statement made by the Chancellor of the Duchy of Lancaster, my right hon. Friend the Member for West Dorset (Mr Letwin) on 21 July 2015 announcing the publication of an updated Cabinet Committees list including a new Economic Affairs (Airports) sub-Committee, <em>Official Report</em>, columns 84WS-85WS.</p><p>Copies of the list are available in the Libraries of the House.</p><p>As with all Cabinet Committees, information relating to the proceedings, including when and how often it meets and which Ministers have attended, is generally not disclosed as to do so would harm the frankness and candour of internal discussion.</p>","Witney","Mr David Cameron",,"2015-10-16T12:26:00.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420274/answer","Biography information for Mr David Cameron","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420274/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420274/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2015-10-09","Cabinet Committees: Airports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, what the (a) date of establishment, (b) membership, (c) meeting schedule and (d) agenda is of the special cabinet committee on airport expansion.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","11025"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420275","Scotland Office","false","2015-10-19","<p>Details of Ministers' andPermanentSecretaries meetings with external organisations are published up to 31March 2015 and can be accessed on Gov.uk at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/ministers-transparency-publications</a></p><br /><p>Further publications of Ministerial and Permanent Secretaries meetings will be published in due course.</p><p><strong></strong></p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-10-19T12:19:38.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420275/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420275/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420275/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-10-09","Scotland Office: Pressure Groups","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what meetings his Department has had with representatives of (a) the Taxpayers' Alliance, (b) the Confederation of British Industry, (c) the Institute of Economic Affairs, (d) the Adam Smith Institute, (e) the Freedom Association, (f) the Politics and Economic Research Trust and (g) the Midlands Industrial Council in the last 12 calendar months.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","10992"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420276","Scotland Office","false","2015-10-19","<p>Both I, my ministerial colleague Lord Dunlop and my officials have met with the STUC, STUC-affiliated trade unions, CoSLA and public bodies over the last six months and discussed a range of matters including trade union reform and the Trade Union Bill. These meetings have taken place on the following dates:</p><ul><li>17 August 2015;</li><li>18 August 2015.</li></ul><p>My Rt hon Friend, Nick Boles, Minister of State for Business Innovation and Skills and officials met with the STUC to discuss trade union reform and the Trade Union Bill on:</p><ul><li>7 September 2015;</li><li>18 August 2015.</li></ul><br />","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-10-19T14:07:13.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420276/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420276/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420276/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-10-09","Trade Unions: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what meetings his Department has had with (a) the Scottish Trade Unions Congress, (b) individual STUC-affiliated trades unions, (c) the Convention of Scottish Local Authorities and (d) other public bodies on trade union reform and the Trade Union Bill in the last six months.","false","Biography information for Chris Stephens","Glasgow South West","Chris Stephens","10991"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420277","Scotland Office","false","2015-10-19","<p>The Scotland Office created and chairs the Scottish Exporting Joint Working Group. This consists of officials from UKTI, SDI and Scottish Enterprise and the Scottish Government. The Group last met on the 5 October where they discussed a draft Action Plan that contains practical steps to achieve greater collaboration, co-operation and alignment between the organisations serving Scottish exporters, in line with the recommendations of the Wilson Review. The Action Plan will be agreed over the coming weeks.</p><p>The Government has no immediate plans to designate the Scotch whisky industry or other sectors in Scotland as free trade champions. However, we are working very closely with the Scotch Whisky Association to learn from their expertise on trade issues with a view to replicating the extraordinary success the Scotch Whisky industry has had in export markets across the wider UK food and drink sector.</p><p><strong></strong></p><br />","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2015-10-19T14:09:05.487Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420277/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420277/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420277/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2015-10-09","Exports: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what progress the Government has made on implementing the recommendations of the Wilson Review of Support for Scottish Exporting; and what plans he has to designate (a) the Scotch whisky industry and (b) other sectors with experience and success in export markets as free trade champions.","false","Biography information for Mr Alistair Carmichael","Orkney and Shetland","Mr Alistair Carmichael","11154"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420278","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2015-10-15","<p>The Electoral Commission does not maintain the electoral registers, which is the statutory duty of Electoral Registration Officers (EROs) and their teams. The Electoral Commission issues guidance to EROs about how to deliver both well run elections and public awareness campaigns to make sure voters are aware of when and how to register to vote. The Commission also runs its own public awareness campaigns to remind people to register to vote and to support the activity of EROs. During its campaign before the 2015 General Election there were 1,561,093 additions to the electoral registers, as detailed in its <a href="http://www.electoralcommission.org.uk/__data/assets/pdf_file/0006/190941/May-2015-polls-public-awareness-activity-report.pdf" target="_blank">campaign evaluation report</a>.</p><p>In June 2015 the Electoral Commission published its assessment of the progress with transition to Individual Electoral Registration (IER). An updated version of this assessment was recently laid in the House Library amending a small number of typographical errors found in background figures, none of which affected the findings of the assessment or the Commission’s advice.</p><p>The Commission’s June IER assessment did not include an estimate of levels of accuracy and completeness of the registers. The Commission’s last report on this was published in 2014. The June report did note, however, that activities such as the introduction of IER and the introduction of online registration are likely to have had a positive impact on accuracy and completeness. However, it was also clear that others will have had a negative effect, such as the lack of comprehensive household canvassing activity in 2014.</p><p>The Electoral Commission has made clear that it does not support the Government’s decision to bring forward the end of the transition to IER to 1 December 2015 and has noted instead that this should remain as 1 December 2016, as Parliament originally decided. However, should Parliament approve the Government’s order to bring forward the end of the transition, the Commission will continue to monitor the state of the registers and will collect further data from EROs focusing on the 2015 canvass and the December 2015 register.</p>","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter",,"2015-10-15T10:09:48.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420278/answer","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420278/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420278/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2015-10-09","Electoral Register","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for South West Devon, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, what assessment the Electoral Commission has made of its performance in ensuring the accuracy of the electoral register during the 2015 General Election.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","10872"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420279","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-14","<p>We will take a decision on future funding for the Bikeability programme beyond March 2016 following the outcome of the Spending Review.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-10-14T13:55:09.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420279/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420279/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420279/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Cycling: Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what his policy in on continued funding for Bikeability in schools after March 2016.","false","Biography information for Nigel Huddleston","Mid Worcestershire","Nigel Huddleston","10878"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420280","HM Treasury","false","2015-10-14","<p>It has been a long standing feature that VED licences are issued from the first day of each month and refunds are issued for whole months of unused tax. Licensing on a date other than the first of the month would add administrative complexity and cost to the tax system. The Government has no plans to change the existing arrangements in place for Vehicle Excise Duty (VED) refunds.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-10-14T14:55:03.047Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420280/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420280/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420280/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-09","Motor Vehicles: Excise Duties","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will introduce a car tax scheme which enables people selling cars to claim back part-months of unused tax payments.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","10884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420281","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-16","<p>All new vehicles are tested in accordance with EU law to ensure that they meet the legislated requirements for emissions. There is no evidence that these emissions tests have been falsified in the UK.</p><p>The UK has been pressing for action at an EU-level to improve emissions tests and will continue to do so. The current test cycle is recognised as outdated and no longer represents normal driving patterns, and we have been involved in the development of a new laboratory test designed to be more representative of real driving conditions. We anticipate this will be implemented from 2017. In addition, we have been at the forefront of action at a European level to introduce real driving emissions (RDE) testing, which we believe is the best way to ensure tests accurately represent performance out on the road and ensure public confidence.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-10-16T11:21:24.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420281/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420281/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420281/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Diesel Vehicles: Exhaust Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that diesel car emissions are tested accurately; and that such emissions tests have not been falsified in the UK.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","10823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420282","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>The A57/A628 Mottram bypass was confirmed in the first Road Investment Strategy in December 2014. Following this, Highways England has started developing its design in more detail. This work involves considering variations for the route, which Highways England will be seeking feedback on from stakeholders, including the local communities through which it passes.</p><p>Before seeking this feedback, Highways England will assess options to establish what impacts they have – both positive and negative - on the environment, the wider network and economy. They will present information from the assessment to the public in the summer of 2016.</p><p>Once this design and assessment work has been completed, the higher-performing options will be put before the public through a consultation process then as part of the statutory planning process. Public consultation is planned for 2017.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-10-15T15:39:13.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420282/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420282/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420282/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Bypasses: Greater Manchester","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent progress there has been on the A57/A628 bypass proposals in the Mottram-in-Longdendale and Hollingworth areas; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Reynolds","Stalybridge and Hyde","Jonathan Reynolds","10834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420283","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-14","<p>The Department introduced the collection of data on personal injury road accidents involving motorised mobility scooters in 2011. A total of 29 out of 44 police forces supplied data in 2014. Across these forces, the number of reported personal injury road accidents involving mobility scooters in 2014 is given in the table below.</p><p><strong></strong></p><p><strong>Number of reported personal injury road accidents involving mobility scooters: GB, 2014</strong></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Severity</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>2014 (1)</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Fatal</p></td><td><p>9</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Serious</p></td><td><p>46</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Slight</p></td><td><p>153</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>All severities</p></td><td><p>208</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>(1) Date from 29 out of 44 police forces</p><p>The Department expects that all forces will supply data by the end of 2016.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-10-14T13:42:50.893Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420283/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420283/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420283/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Invalid Vehicles: Accidents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many accidents were reported involving mobility scooters in 2014.","false","Biography information for Kate Hollern","Blackburn","Kate Hollern","10859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420284","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>The Secretary of State asked the new Chairman of Network Rail, Sir Peter Hendy, to review the delivery of all projects across the entire Rail enhancements portfolio.</p><p>In the Blackpool North electrification scheme as it is currently defined, the connecting points will be removed from their current location as they restrict speed on a sharp curve towards Blackpool, but an allowance has been made in the design for a new, ‎simpler, connection, should the need arise to reconnect the line in future.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","10718","2015-10-15T13:29:50.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420284/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420284/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420284/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Railways: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent discussions he has had with Network Rail on the electrification of the Blackpool North railway line and the proposed removal of points which connect this line with a disused railway line connecting Poulton-le-Fylde to Fleetwood.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","10794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420285","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>Network Rail have now finished assessing options for an accessible route at Stechford and will begin detailed design next month. Work should start on site late next year and take around eight months to complete.</p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2015-10-15T15:34:48.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420285/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420285/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420285/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Stechford Station","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the accessibility alterations for Stechford Railway Station will begin.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","10706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420286","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>The Department for Transport has issued guidance to the licensed trade on the provisions in the Equality Act that require taxis and private hire vehicles to carry guide and other assistance dogs.</p><p>In addition to their ability to take appropriate action in the event that licensed drivers fail to comply with this duty, local licensing authorities can inform taxi and private hire drivers of all their responsibilities as licensed drivers.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-10-15T14:32:52.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420286/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420286/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420286/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Taxis","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps he is taking to ensure that taxi operators and drivers in private hire vehicles are aware of their legal obligation to grant access to blind or partially-sighted people with guide dogs.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","10734"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420287","HM Treasury","false","2015-10-16","<p>In light of the decision to devolve APD to Scotland and consider the case for devolving APD to Wales, the government has recently published a discussion paper exploring options to support English regional airports from the impacts of APD devolution. We are considering the evidence that we have received from stakeholders, and will respond to the consultation in due course.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2015-10-16T13:40:58.267Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420287/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420287/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420287/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-09","Regional Airports: Air Passenger Duty","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what recent assessment he has made of the effect of devolution of air passenger duty on regional airports.","false","Biography information for Ben Howlett","Bath","Ben Howlett","10730"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420288","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>No discussions have taken place with the European Commission on potential state aid or future public funding requirements for any of the three schemes shortlisted by the Airports Commission.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-10-15T09:58:11.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420288/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420288/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420288/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Heathrow Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what preliminary discussion his Department has had with the European Commission on potential state aid issues relating to future public funding requirements for a new runway at Heathrow airport.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","10739"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420289","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>The Secretary of State asked the new Chairman of Network Rail, Sir Peter Hendy, to review the delivery of all projects across the entire Rail enhancements portfolio.</p><p>In the Blackpool North electrification scheme as it is currently defined, the connecting points will be removed from their current location as they restrict speed on a sharp curve towards Blackpool, but an allowance has been made in the design for a new, ‎simpler, connection, should the need arise to reconnect the line in future.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones","10794","2015-10-15T13:29:50.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420289/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420289/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420289/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Railways: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will arrange to retain the points connecting Poulton-le-Fylde's disused railway line to Fleetwood.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","10718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420290","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>This Government believes that local authorities and Local Enterprise Partnerships (LEPs) are best placed to decide on, and take forward, transport schemes which will most benefit their local area. In 2013 the Government established a £12bn Local Growth Fund (LGF) to support LEPs in delivering their priorities for supporting local economic growth. The Government has since awarded significant LGF funding through the Growth Deals, including £251m to Lancashire LEP, to enable local schemes to be taken forward.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-10-15T15:42:35.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420290/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420290/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420290/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Railways: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans his Department has for the reopening of disused railway lines in Lancashire.","false","Biography information for Cat Smith","Lancaster and Fleetwood","Cat Smith","10719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420291","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-14","<p>The Department for Transport (DfT), along with its local partners, is involved in considering options for a long term site to be used as part of Operation Stack in the future. Disclosing commercially sensitive information such as the costs and tenure involved in the use of Manston Airfield, would be prejudicial to the DfT in securing value for money, through commercial negotiations, for the temporary solution and a long term site.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-10-14T14:10:57.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420291/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420291/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420291/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Manston Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, under what cost and tenure an agreement from the owners of Manston Air Field for that field to be used under Operation Stack was secured; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","10723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420292","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-14","<p>On 4 August 2015, we announced that we had secured Manston Airfield as a viable short term solution to relieve pressure on the M20 during Operation Stack whilst the Government was considering a range of short to long term solutions.</p><p>Highways England is considering a number of sites off the strategic road network which could offer a potential long term solution. The work on this is moving at pace but no final decisions have been made.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2015-10-14T14:32:48.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420292/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420292/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420292/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Manston Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether Manston Airfield will continue to be used under Operation Stack; what alternatives are under review; and what consultation under which timeframe is ongoing into the work of Operation Stack.","false","Biography information for Richard Burden","Birmingham, Northfield","Richard Burden","10724"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420293","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>The Government continues to consider the large amount of very detailed analysis contained in the Airports Commission’s final report, including its examination of the costs and financing of the schemes, before taking any decisions on next steps.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2015-10-15T10:16:22.287Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420293/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420293/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420293/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Heathrow Airport","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 18 September 2015 to Question 10131, what preliminary work his Department is undertaking to assess the public funding requirement of, and potential state aid issues related to, a new runway at Heathrow Airport before making any decision on next steps.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","10777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420294","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>The certification of aero-engines is primarily the responsibility of the certification authority for the state of manufacture. In Europe this is the European Aviation Safety Agency (EASA) who also have oversight of engines certified in other regions that expect to be registered in the UK or any other European country. We are in discussion with EASA as to how we might be reassured that the results for aviation certifications are robust. The certification requirement for Oxides of Nitrogen (NOx), Carbon Monoxide and unburnt hydrocarbon is based on operating the engine on a test bed at different thrust settings to simulate the landing and take-off phases of flight below 3000 feet. The visible smoke test identifies the worst case condition for smoke. A new standard for CO2 emissions from aircraft is being developed and is expected to assess the cruise emissions as this phase dominates total fuel burn. EASA certification engineers would verify the fuel burn on tightly controlled test flights. The Secretary of State informed the Transport Select Committee on 12th October that the current focus of the Government’s investigation into the use of defeat devices is focussed on cars and light commercial vehicles.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","11163 ; 11164","2015-10-15T13:47:08.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420294/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420294/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/420294/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-09","Aircraft: Exhaust Emissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will take steps to ensure that assessments of emissions from aero-engines in use in the UK used by his Department are independently verified as reflective of real-world conditions of use.","false","Biography information for Zac Goldsmith","Richmond Park","Zac Goldsmith","11165"
