"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419685","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-10-19","<p>The Government has no intention of imposing any arrangements for the next round of ERDF ‘JEREMIE’ style Access to Finance funds that do not carry local support.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2015-10-19T13:47:54.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419685/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419685/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419685/answer",,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-10-05","Small Businesses: EU Grants and Loans","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they plan to divert part or all of the £160m JEREMIE (Joint European Resources for Micro to medium Enterprises) 2 fund, succeeding the Finance for Business North East fund, to other Northern areas described as part of the Northern Powerhouse; and if so, what proportion of funding will be diverted, and why they are taking such action.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL2388"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419686","HM Treasury","false","2015-10-19","<p>Her Majesty’s Government has not instructed local authorities on the matter of disclosing the contents of their submissions for the Comprehensive Spending Review. Local authorities are free to publish the contents of their submissions and many have chosen to do so.</p><br />",,"Lord O'Neill of Gatley",,"2015-10-19T15:31:40.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419686/answer","Biography information for Lord O'Neill of Gatley","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419686/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419686/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2015-10-05","Public Expenditure","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they instructed local authorities not to disclose the contents of their submissions for the Comprehensive Spending Review; and, if so, why.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL2389"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419687","Ministry of Justice","false","2015-10-27","<p>MTC and their main partner Amey were subject to robust and rigorous assessment at the pre-qualification stage of the competition. This included a thorough examination of health and safety, equalities, human rights and discrimination policies, and a requirement to demonstrate their experience of managing children and young people.</p><br /><p>There were no findings of a breach in human rights or equality legislation.</p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2015-10-27T16:23:25.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419687/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419687/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419687/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2015-10-05","Rainsbrook Secure Training Centre","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in relation to the decision to award MTCNovo the contract to run Rainsbrook Secure Training Centre, what assessment they have made of the experience that company has in running residential establishments that care for vulnerable children; and whether MTCNovo, including its partners or significant subcontractors, has been found to have breached human rights or equality legislation in the last three years, either in the United Kingdom or abroad.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL2390"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419688","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>Contracts between the Department for Transport and Agility Trains and Great Western Rail are commercially confidential.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2015-10-15T10:50:44.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419688/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419688/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419688/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-05","Great Western Railway Line","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how much Network Rail, the Department for Transport, First Great Western and Agility trains have each committed to contributing to the £7.5 billion Great Western route modernisation programme.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL2391"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419689","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>Network Rail is an arm’s-length public sector body and the sources of funding contributions towards the construction of the new bridge are a commercial matter for the company.</p><p>Network Rail advises that the new bridge across the South West Mainline was privately funded by one organisation. Network Rail has signed a confidentially agreement with this organisation which does not allow the release of commercial information.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2015-10-15T10:51:13.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419689/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419689/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419689/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-05","Railways: Bridges","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government which organisations are contributing to the new bridge across the South Western Main Line south of Clapham Junction station giving access to Emanuel School, and how much they are each contributing.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL2392"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419690","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>In general the normal limiting gradient on the proposed HS2 line is 2.5%, which occurs at various locations along the route.</p><p>However, there are a few instances of steeper gradients where there are physical constraints that do not allow gradients of 2.5% or less to be achieved, namely:</p><p>- Between Euston Station and Euston Tunnels (3.4%)</p><p>- In the Euston Tunnels before Old Oak Common (3.5%)</p><p>- The east end of the Bromford Tunnel (2.9%)</p><p>- The approach to Birmingham Curzon St (3.03%)</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2015-10-15T10:51:53.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419690/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419690/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419690/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-05","High Speed 2 Railway Line","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what are the maximum gradients on the proposed HS2 line, and where they are located.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL2393"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419691","Department for Transport","false","2015-10-15","<p>Although it has made no specific assessment, the Government is well aware of the disruptive impact of migrants seeking to access the UK across the English Channel, both through the Channel Tunnel and on the shipping routes. The impact at the Channel Tunnel is particularly severe on the rail freight operators, who have seen a significant reduction in their business, and on Eurotunnel itself.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2015-10-15T10:53:23.343Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419691/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419691/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/419691/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2015-10-05","Channel Tunnel: Undocumented Migrants","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the effect on UK business of the continuing disruption by migrants of rail and road freight traffic through the Channel Tunnel.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL2394"
